Consider the region bounded by three circular arcs of radius 5 units. Arcs $AB$ and $AD$ are quarter-circles, and arc $BCD$ is a semicircle, as shown in the diagram below: egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) .. controls (1,1) .. (2,0);\draw (0,0) .. controls (.7,-.3) .. (1,-1);\draw (1,-1) .. controls (1.3, -0.3) .. (2,0);
ode[below left] at (1,-1) {$A$};
ode[left] at (0,0) {$B$};
ode[above] at (1,1) {$C$};
ode[right] at (2,0) {$D$};\end{tikzpicture}What is the area, in square units, of the region?
